    <note>Huang(2) Daming [858] In 1108, he was recommended (juren or jie) #1. For lineage identification, see Sanshan zhi, 31.2a [Huang(2) Xuan(2)]. Daming's nephew, Xuan(2) [19018], was a Luoyuan county resident as was his lineage kin Xu(2) [19023], son of Weize [19022]. Xuan(2)'s elder brother, Qian(2) [19019], was a Houguan county resident. Qian(2)'s nephew, Anzhi [19021], who was also a nephew of Mi [19020], both of whom were a Yongtai county residents. Chronological logic and documentation makes Weize a lineage nephew of Daming, who moved to Luoyuan, Xuan(2) a documented nephew, who moved to Luoyan, Mi, a nephew, who remained in Yongfu (Yongtai), and Qian(2) was a nephew, who moved to Houguan. Sanshan zhi, 27.13b; SHY:ZG, 45.19b. CBD, 4, 2884.</note>
